⚙️ Simple Self-Induction Protocol (try this)

1. Set the Frame (important)

Tell yourself (literally):

“I’m going to shift my state intentionally. I’m safe. I can stop anytime.”

This removes resistance and boosts effect.

⸻

2. Breath Loop (2–3 minutes)

Do this rhythm:
	•	Inhale (nose): 4 seconds
	•	Hold: 4 seconds
	•	Exhale (mouth): 6–8 seconds
	•	Pause: 2 seconds

After ~10–15 cycles:
	•	Body starts to feel lighter or warmer
	•	Slight floaty feeling may begin

⸻

3. Attention Lock

Pick one:
	•	Focus on your hands
	•	Or the feeling behind your eyes
	•	Or your heartbeat

Then:

Don’t analyze. Just sit inside the sensation.

This is where the shift deepens.

⸻

4. Sensory Amplification

Now layer in suggestion (this is the “lever”):

Tell yourself slowly:
	•	“My body is getting lighter”
	•	“Everything feels slightly delayed”
	•	“There’s a hum under everything”

Don’t force belief—just offer it and observe

Your brain will start simulating it.

⸻

5. Micro-Dissociation (optional but powerful)

Close your eyes and imagine:
	•	Your body is slightly bigger than it is
	•	Or slightly smaller
	•	Or your hands are farther away than they should be

This can create that “altered” feeling very quickly.

⸻

6. Let Go Phase

Stop trying.

Just sit in it for 1–3 minutes.

That’s usually where:
	•	Time distortion
	•	Calm/euphoria
	•	Floaty sensation

kicks in.

⸻

⚠️ Important Guardrails
	•	Don’t overdo breath holds (avoid dizziness beyond mild)
	•	Stay seated or lying down
	•	If it feels off → just breathe normally and open your eyes

